---
// Mission Section Component
---

<section id="mission" class="section mission-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="mission-header">
      <h2>Artagon Identity Platform: Architecting the Future of Digital Trust</h2>
      <p class="mission-tagline">
        Trusted identity for machines and humans — <strong>Verified. Private. Attested.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mission-intro-text">
      <p>
        The digital world is in an identity crisis. Perimeter security failed, and identity is split between human‑centric CIAM and ad‑hoc machine identity (M2M/IoT)—creating breach risk, friction, and eroding privacy.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Artagon is not another IdP.</strong> It's a next‑generation trust infrastructure that unifies three historically siloed domains:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid cols-3 mission-domains">
      <div class="card domain-highlight">
        <div class="domain-badge">01</div>
        <h3>High‑Assurance Identity</h3>
        <p>Passkey‑primary, phishing‑resistant authentication built on modern OpenID Connect and GNAP.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card domain-highlight">
        <div class="domain-badge">02</div>
        <h3>Decentralized & Verifiable Identity</h3>
        <p>A full Verifiable Credentials (VC) engine for issuing and verifying portable, holder‑controlled, privacy‑preserving credentials.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card domain-highlight">
        <div class="domain-badge">03</div>
        <h3>Next‑Generation Authorization</h3>
        <p>A high‑performance, graph‑based engine that fuses Zanzibar‑style ReBAC with Cedar/OPA (ABAC) for fine‑grained, contextual decisions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mission-divider"></div>

    <div class="mission-difference">
      <h3>The Artagon Difference</h3>
      <div class="grid difference-grid">
        <div class="card pillar-card">
          <div class="pill-number">1</div>
          <h4>Verifiable Everything</h4>
          <p>Move from "asserted" to proven identity. Every attribute, device, and software client is cryptographically verifiable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card pillar-card">
          <div class="pill-number">2</div>
          <h4>Zero‑Friction Security</h4>
          <p>Make the most secure path the easiest: passwordless passkey‑primary login and invisible, hardware‑level device & app attestation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card pillar-card">
          <div class="pill-number">3</div>
          <h4>Privacy‑by‑Design</h4>
          <p>Selective disclosure (zero‑knowledge) lets users prove facts (e.g., "over 18") without exposing raw PII. Privacy is built into the protocol, not bolted on.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mission-divider"></div>

    <div class="platform-highlights">
      <h3>Platform Highlights</h3>
      <div class="grid cols-2 highlights-grid">
        <div class="card highlight-card">
          <h4>Unified Identity & Authorization Core</h4>
          <p>Modern OIDC + GNAP with hardened profiles and cryptographic multi‑tenancy by default.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card highlight-card">
          <h4>Verifiable Credentials, Seamlessly Bridged</h4>
          <p>Issue and verify VCs—and bridge legacy OIDC apps via OID4VC/OID4VP so they gain high‑assurance data with no rewrites.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card highlight-card">
          <h4>Device & Application Attestation</h4>
          <p>Bind trust to hardware; bind tokens/keys to devices so stolen tokens are useless.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card highlight-card">
          <h4>Hybrid Authorization (ReBAC + ABAC)</h4>
          <p>Zanzibar graph for relationships; Cedar/OPA policies for context and conditions; all managed as policy‑as‑code with an auditable trail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mission-divider"></div>

    <div class="authority-broker">
      <h3>From Identity Provider to Authority Broker</h3>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Artagon enables <strong>Verifiable Authority</strong>—precise, time‑bound, auditable delegation across teams and domains:
      </p>
      <div class="use-cases">
        <div class="use-case">
          <h4>Customer Service, done right</h4>
          <p>A CSR securely acts on behalf of a customer with explicit, time‑boxed consent—no admin backdoors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="use-case">
          <h4>Cross‑organization access</h4>
          <p>A doctor grants a specialist temporary read‑only access to a specific file—no brittle federations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="use-case">
          <h4>IAM for AI</h4>
          <p>A CFO authorizes an AI agent to sign contracts under $50,000—human‑issued authority with cryptographic guardrails.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mission-divider"></div>

    <div class="why-artagon">
      <div class="grid cols-2">
        <div class="why-card">
          <h3>Why Enterprises Choose Artagon</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Slash risk:</strong> Eliminate the #1 phishing vector with passkeys, attestation, and token binding.</li>
            <li><strong>Prove compliance:</strong> A clear path to verifiable frameworks (e.g., NIST, eIDAS) with proofing and auditable decisions.</li>
            <li><strong>Future‑proof:</strong> Bridge today's OIDC world to decentralized, verifiable identity—without rip‑and‑replace.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="why-card">
          <h3>Why Developers Love It</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>One Trust API</strong> that abstracts crypto, protocols, attestation, and authorization.</li>
            <li><strong>Polyglot SDKs,</strong> CLI, and Docs‑as‑Code playgrounds to go from hello world to high assurance fast.</li>
            <li><strong>Git‑backed policy‑as‑code</strong> and conformance harnesses out of the box.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vision-cta-links">
      <a class="btn" href="/vision/">Read Full Vision & Roadmap</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/roadmap/">View 18-Month Roadmap</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.mission-section {
  background: linear-gradient(
    180deg,
    var(--bg) 0%,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-teal) 2%, var(--bg)) 50%,
    var(--bg) 100%
  );
}

.mission-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.mission-header h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  color: var(--text);
}

.mission-tagline {
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  color: var(--brand-teal);
  margin: 0;
}

.mission-intro-text {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.mission-intro-text p {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.mission-intro-text strong {
  color: var(--text);
  font-weight: 600;
}

.mission-domains {
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.mission-divider {
  height: 1px;
  background: linear-gradient(
    90deg,
    transparent 0%,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--border) 60%, transparent) 50%,
    transparent 100%
  );
  margin: 3rem 0;
}

.mission-difference h3,
.platform-highlights h3,
.authority-broker h3 {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  color: var(--brand-teal);
}

.difference-grid {
  gap: 1.5rem;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .difference-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}

.highlights-grid {
  gap: 1.5rem;
}

.highlight-card {
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 95%, var(--brand-teal) 5%);
  border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-teal) 20%, transparent);
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.highlight-card:hover {
  border-color: var(--brand-teal);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
}

.highlight-card h4 {
  color: var(--brand-teal);
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
}

.highlight-card p {
  color: var(--muted);
  margin: 0;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.section-intro {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto 2rem;
}

.use-cases {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin-top: 2rem;
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .use-cases {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}

.use-case {
  padding: 1.5rem;
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 90%, transparent);
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--border) 60%, transparent);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.use-case:hover {
  border-color: var(--brand-violet);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}

.use-case h4 {
  color: var(--brand-violet);
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  font-size: 1.05rem;
}

.use-case p {
  color: var(--muted);
  margin: 0;
  line-height: 1.6;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
}

.why-card {
  padding: 2rem;
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 90%, transparent);
  border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--border) 60%, transparent);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
}

.why-card h3 {
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  color: var(--text);
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  text-align: left;
}

.why-card ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}

.why-card li {
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  position: relative;
}

.why-card li::before {
  content: '→';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--brand-teal);
  font-weight: bold;
}

.why-card strong {
  color: var(--text);
}

.vision-cta-links {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  justify-content: center;
  margin-top: 3rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
</style>
